---
description: Avoid instructional or guiding copy in the product UI and in code meant for end users.
alwaysApply: true
---

# No instructional or guiding copy

When changing or adding UI, source strings, or user-visible text in code:

- Do not add “how to” panels, onboarding hints, tutorial paragraphs, or step-by-step guidance unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Prefer short labels, button text, and field names without explanatory prose.
- Do not add comment blocks or strings whose only purpose is to teach the user how to use the app; use code structure and minimal labels instead.
